$interpreted: Chiyuki: Thank you, ladies and gentlemen, for coming all the way to Feihua City.
Chiyuki: As everyone is aware, we will be trudging through these treacherous lands today to pick the last remaining tournament finalist.
Chiyuki: But before that~
Excited Audience: Alliance Beauty! Alliance Beauty!
Chiyuki: That’s right, so without further ado~
Hestia: Look, Puggi, they’re about to reveal the votes!
Puggi: (...How should I use ‘this’ on Pang later...)
Hestia: Puggi? Puggi? Quit spacing out!
Chiyuki: (…Weird, why is he so quiet today?)
Chiyuki: The current vote count is...
Excited Audience: Chiyuki! Chiyuki!
Noisy Audience: Weird bird! Weird bird!
Chiyuki: Don’t worry, last time was just a fluke… an unhappy accident...
Excited Audience: Chiyuki... Chiyuki...
Noisy Audience: Weird bird! Weird bird! Weird bird!
???: Puggipuggipuggi~
Chiyuki: No! Go away!
Chiyuki: No!
Chiyuki: I’ll never let you─
Chiyuki: The current Alliance Beauty frontrunner is─
Chiyuki: Pu! Gi!?
Chiyuki: It’s over... Chiyuki...
Chiyuki: Her reign of radiance... has been... eclipsed...
Excited Audience: Damn, we were so close!
Excited Audience: And we got so many people to vote for Chiyuki, too!
Chiyuki: (It’s true, the count was so much closer than last time... I almost won...)
Excited Audience: It's alright, the competition still isn’t over! It’s the final vote that counts!
Chiyuki: (They’re being so supportive... is that because they think I could really lose?)
Chiyuki: (No... It’s not over! I’m still in this, and I’m in it to win it!)
Chiyuki: Thank you everyone for your support! Puggi may be in front, but the voting isn’t over, yet! There’s one more chance to cast your votes!
Chiyuki: So, don’t give up, everyone! Vote for your heart’s true Alliance Beauty!
Chiyuki: (You see that, you stupid bird? I’ll never lose to you...)
Chiyuki: (...Puggi?)
Puggi: Where’s Pang~!?
Alliance Soldier: You must be exhausted, Miss Chiyuki.
Alliance Soldier: Take a rest. When the arena is set up, we’ll inform you.
Chiyuki: Okay, thank you very much.
Chiyuki: (So, he ran over here.)
Puggi: Found you!
Puggi: Locked on target! Ready, aim─
Puggi: Fire!!
Puggi: Got you!
Pang: It's you!?
Puggi: Yagh! Let... me... down...
Puggi: Whew... you almost just ended season 3 early, you big lug!
Pang: ...What are you doing in the contestant rest area once again?
Puggi: I’m the Main Character, little bro! I can go wherever I want!
Pang: ...Listen, I’m not in the mood to play your games right now.
Puggi: But wait, Pang! I have something important to tell you!!
Pang: Your demeanor tells me otherwise.
Puggi: That’s cold, Pang! That’s cold! Just listen─
Chiyuki: (How is it that they can be so playful, so close…)
Pang: I told you already, I’m not in the mood!
Puggi: Bwah, I’ve been vanquished! When will the MC get another chance...?
Chiyuki: Is this yours?
Puggi: Eh!? Yeah, it is!
Puggi: Oh, I remember you... you’re one of my supporting characters! Well, thank you very much, oh trusty sidekick!
Chiyuki: ...Don’t mention it.
Chiyuki: By the way, you seem to have quite a close relationship with Mr. Pang.
Puggi: Well, duh~ I mean, he’s my little bro, after all.
Chiyuki: Ah... I see. So, you don't worry about how it might... look? To fraternize with him?
Puggi: How it might look? What are you talking about?
Chiyuki: I mean, you’re loved by all. You’re the Alliance Beauty frontrunner. Celebrities like you shouldn’t be schmoozing with just anybody.
Chiyuki: No matter how much they adore you... how much they want to be your friend. You still can’t...
Chiyuki: Otherwise, they might change their mind about you...
Puggi: Bwaha~ Frankly, my dear, I don’t know what the heck you’re talking about! Sounds like a bunch of nonsense!
Chiyuki: N-Nonsense!? What about it is nonsense!?
Puggi: Well, I mean, you’re wrong! It’s not Pang that wants to be friends with me...
Puggi: It's me who wants to be friends with Pang!
Chiyuki: But... but how!?
Puggi: What do you mean, ‘how’? If you wanna be friends with someone, you’ve got to put in the work! Make yourself available! Invite them out for tea!
Chiyuki: (W-What? Is it really... so easy? All of this trouble I’ve put myself through...)
Puggi: Yep, that’s all well and dandy, making friends. It’s easier than... than ‘this’, anyway...
Chiyuki: Easier than what…?
Puggi: Well, I’m in the middle of finding an opportunity to get Pang to use this ‘good stuff’~
Chiyuki: (Huh... something seems fishy about this...)
Chiyuki: Ah... Yes, I’m quite aware of that... ‘good stuff’.
Puggi: Oh really? Well, doesn’t matter... I’ll get my chance soon enough~
Chiyuki: Whew... I’ve got no idea what that crazy bird was talking about, but... be careful, Pang. Even if you are friends...
